<subSubSection id="8729AC776283CDFAC056CE3DBF76BDB6" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="69AC91DAD543E38B8CA251FEB20EAC0E" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D6A665E7471B483B2043971AFFDE9B9" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<normalizedToken id="F6E1CA63182DA29C1112790C15D2E0DC" originalValue="“…">&quot;...</normalizedToken>
can be distinguished from all other zoantharians including 
<taxonomicName id="8B8A2B6C8C4B8FBD8E2CBC57A4CA0369" authorityName="Haddon &amp; Shackelton" authorityYear="1891" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Parazoanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parazoanthus" order="Zoantharia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="303EBDCF9F11A6B9D5B13E45AD627B73" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Parazoanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., 
<taxonomicName id="93277F5FED354D8A48A5664C625EE56B" authorityName="Montenegro, Sinniger &amp; Reimer" authorityYear="2015" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Umimayanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Umimayanthus" order="Zoantharia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCF5B5646B906E1ECD470FA302C2DD70" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Umimayanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. and 
<taxonomicName id="2E1C67A3B5AE4278C0045EBDE00976DF" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" class="Anthozoa" family="Epizoanthidae" genus="Epizoanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epizoanthus" order="Zoantharia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E11BC7495AF6821BC367EE80FE1849B1" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Epizoanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. by a unique deletion of 60 bp (from position 133 to 192 in our alignment) and several consecutive base substitutions in the 16S-rDNA region. These characters clearly separate this genus from all other genera inside the family 
<taxonomicName id="2EE8910212F36F140A23D645F6D24F15" authorityName="Delage &amp; Herouard" authorityYear="1901" family="Parazoanthidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Zoantharia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="family">Parazoanthidae</taxonomicName>
, as well as from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="79BE245887323BFAAE5493F4F98A671A" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" class="Anthozoa" family="Epizoanthidae" genus="Epizoanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epizoanthus" order="Zoantharia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3E9A635D98DF777FD287F0F4903DF518" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Epizoanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="2928826B51269C441285947C2852573F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2015.1101028" author="Montenegro, J" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="B192" refString="Montenegro, J, Low, MEY, Reimer, JD, 2015a. The resurrection of the genus Bergia Duchassaing and Michelotti, 1860 (Anthozoa, Zoantharia, Parazoanthidae. Systematics and Biodiversity 14(1): 63-73. https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2015.1101028" title="The resurrection of the genus Bergia Duchassaing and Michelotti, 1860 (Anthozoa, Zoantharia, Parazoanthidae. Systematics and Biodiversity 14 (1): 63 - 73." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2015.1101028" year="2015 a">Montenegro et al. 2015a</bibRefCitation>
: 68).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BF2BB00581D84F5302D8803B8F36BAF8" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="9FD9CFD0A99CF9A634C47309E58FD747" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CBD1125C7E2B4796B41EB9ED19838D11" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Long considered to be a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="AC89B1462333A3606AC757E71D9A41E9" authorityName="Haddon &amp; Shackelton" authorityYear="1891" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Parazoanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parazoanthus" order="Zoantharia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BC411F80658C399EC2309C837AF0A48" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Parazoanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Haddon &amp; Shackelton, 1891, recent molecular and morphological work by 
<bibRefCitation id="05C9DE1489EB72865E509BB4326416B8" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2015.1101028" author="Montenegro, J" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="B192" refString="Montenegro, J, Low, MEY, Reimer, JD, 2015a. The resurrection of the genus Bergia Duchassaing and Michelotti, 1860 (Anthozoa, Zoantharia, Parazoanthidae. Systematics and Biodiversity 14(1): 63-73. https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2015.1101028" title="The resurrection of the genus Bergia Duchassaing and Michelotti, 1860 (Anthozoa, Zoantharia, Parazoanthidae. Systematics and Biodiversity 14 (1): 63 - 73." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2015.1101028" year="2015 a">Montenegro et al. (2015a)</bibRefCitation>
have shown that the type species, 
<taxonomicName id="9955AF105DB1147C170013602B42F19A" authorityName="Duchassaing de Fonbressin &amp; Michelotti" authorityYear="1860" class="Hoplonemertea" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Bergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bergia catenularis" order="Zoantharia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="catenularis">
<emphasis id="6FCBA14B250AAF4D125B2A35BCA8769A" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Bergia catenularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Duchassaing de Fonbressin &amp; Michelotti, 1860, represents a generic-level monophyly and resurrected the genus-group name 
<taxonomicName id="F9122AA2717B4FFDCF1AF9C41A9A5CB6" authorityName="Duchassaing de Fonbressin &amp; Michelotti" authorityYear="1860" class="Hoplonemertea" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Bergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bergia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Nemertea" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDE34D0F11223468D3CD7CB64C03C25A" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Bergia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Duchassaing de Fonbressin &amp; Michelotti, 1860, for this grouping.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4562CBE09728E2076703684649D725EF" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
This genus-grouping currently contains three species all found in the Atlantic Ocean, although there is evidence of undescribed species in the Pacific Ocean (
<bibRefCitation id="206A6A8DAFC307099B39A8BFE30EEF80" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2015.1101028" author="Montenegro, J" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="B192" refString="Montenegro, J, Low, MEY, Reimer, JD, 2015a. The resurrection of the genus Bergia Duchassaing and Michelotti, 1860 (Anthozoa, Zoantharia, Parazoanthidae. Systematics and Biodiversity 14(1): 63-73. https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2015.1101028" title="The resurrection of the genus Bergia Duchassaing and Michelotti, 1860 (Anthozoa, Zoantharia, Parazoanthidae. Systematics and Biodiversity 14 (1): 63 - 73." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/14772000.2015.1101028" year="2015 a">Montenegro et al. 2015a</bibRefCitation>
: 68).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC0F8091F868E9D24EAF7696DD0262A3" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Examined species in this genus-grouping have either branchiform endodermal or simplified mesogleal sphincter muscles (
<bibRefCitation id="4F8D1C8A137011EAD4530D35B3EB7F85" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12862-015-0406-1" author="Swain, TD" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="B284" refString="Swain, TD, Schellinger, JL, Strimaitis, AM, Reuter, KE, 2015. Evolution of anthozoan polyp retraction mechanisms: convergent functional morphology and evolutionary allometry of the marginal musculature in order Zoanthidea (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia). BMC Evolutionary Biology 15(123): 1-19. https://doi.org/10.1186/s12862-015-0406-1" title="Evolution of anthozoan polyp retraction mechanisms: convergent functional morphology and evolutionary allometry of the marginal musculature in order Zoanthidea (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia). BMC Evolutionary Biology 15 (123): 1 - 19." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12862-015-0406-1" year="2015">Swain et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
